  <data key="d4">"The actual amount paid by Medicare beneficiaries for covered drugs, tracked by the contracted entity."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b14ea02aabc3c1d74ff07de937978aa9</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PLAN BIDS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"DOCUMENT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Plan bids are submissions made by PDP Sponsors to offer plans in a region."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a8d49cc5f599bfb3f6f139071bb0cfac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FORMULARY EXCEPTIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PROCESS"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A process allowing exceptions to a plan’s formulary for specific medications."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-647561dd6831e3ae72c2d43faf5b0b9f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OTHER LAWS AND REGULATIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A general reference to additional legal requirements beyond those explicitly listed, which the PDP Sponsor must comply with."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-b14ea02aabc3c1d74ff07de937978aa9</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DATA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Data must be transferred in a timely manner when a contract is not renewed."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a8d49cc5f599bfb3f6f139071bb0cfac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SUBPART U&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"REGULATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Federal regulation related to appeals and grievances in Medicare Part D."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-647561dd6831e3ae72c2d43faf5b0b9f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WAIVER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"DOCUMENT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A temporary exemption from state licensing requirements granted under 42 CFR § 423.410."&lt;SEP&gt;"A waiver is a temporary authorization granted under 42 CFR § 423.415, allowing a PDP Sponsor to operate in a state without full qualification, valid for up to one year, beginning January 1 of the contract year, to allow time for processing of the license application."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d33402aba37c5664514afa00a872b8ae&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-647561dd6831e3ae72c2d43faf5b0b9f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FILES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Files must be transferred in a timely manner when a contract is not renewed."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a8d49cc5f599bfb3f6f139071bb0cfac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SUBPART G OF 42 CFR PART 423&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"REGULATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Federal regulation governing payment rules for Medicare Part D contracts."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-647561dd6831e3ae72c2d43faf5b0b9f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SECRETARY OF THE DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The Secretary of the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services (HHS) is the federal official responsible for determining the appropriate validity period of a waiver, ensuring sufficient time for timely processing of a PDP Sponsor's license application by the state, with a maximum duration of one year."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d33402aba37c5664514afa00a872b8ae</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;42 CFR § 423.507(A)(5)&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"REGULATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A federal regulation that mandates the timely transfer of data and files."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a8d49cc5f599bfb3f6f139071bb0cfac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CLAIMS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PROCESS"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The formal submission and processing of requests for payment for covered services."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-647561dd6831e3ae72c2d43faf5b0b9f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;42 CFR § 423.415&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"REGULATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"This regulation governs the issuance and validity of waivers for PDP Sponsors operating in states, allowing temporary operation while awaiting full state licensing, with a maximum one-year validity period."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d33402aba37c5664514afa00a872b8ae</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DEADLINE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"TIME PERIOD"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A deadline is set in 42 CFR § 423.507(a)(2)(i) for submitting a request to end the contract."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a8d49cc5f599bfb3f6f139071bb0cfac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DEBT COLLECTIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PROCESS"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The process of recovering overpayments made to PDP Sponsors."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-647561dd6831e3ae72c2d43faf5b0b9f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LICENSE APPLICATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"DOCUMENT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A formal request submitted by a PDP Sponsor to a state for authorization to operate a Part D plan. The waiver period is intended to allow timely processing of this application."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d33402aba37c5664514afa00a872b8ae</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;42 CFR § 423.507(A)(2)(I)&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"REGULATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A federal regulation that sets a deadline for contract termination requests."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a8d49cc5f599bfb3f6f139071bb0cfac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OVERPAID MONIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"FINANCIAL ASSET"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Funds paid to a PDP Sponsor that exceed the amount owed, requiring repayment."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-647561dd6831e3ae72c2d43faf5b0b9f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CONTRACT YEAR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"TIME PERIOD"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A contract year is the annual period beginning January 1 during which a waiver is granted by CMS, and the validity of the waiver is tied to this timeframe."&lt;SEP&gt;"The annual period covered by the PDP contract, during which the Medical Loss Ratio data is collected and reported."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-89bdab9933b704535281ee7396b3c0c8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d33402aba37c5664514afa00a872b8ae</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MEDICARE PART D PROGRAM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PROGRAM"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The Medicare Part D Program provides prescription drug coverage to eligible individuals."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a8d49cc5f599bfb3f6f139071bb0cfac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PART D PROGRAM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PROGRAM"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Medicare Part D, a federal program providing prescription drug coverage."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-647561dd6831e3ae72c2d43faf5b0b9f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SPAPS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"State Pharmacy Assistance Programs (SPAPs) are state-level programs that assist low-income individuals with prescription drug costs. PDP Sponsors must coordinate with these programs to ensure proper benefit alignment."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d33402aba37c5664514afa00a872b8ae</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GENERAL PUBLIC&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The general public refers to all individuals who may be affected by the contract termination."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a8d49cc5f599bfb3f6f139071bb0cfac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PREMIUMS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"FINANCIAL TERM"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The amount beneficiaries pay monthly for Part D coverage."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-647561dd6831e3ae72c2d43faf5b0b9f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OTHER PRESCRIPTION DRUG COVERAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"This refers to any additional prescription drug coverage provided by other plans, such as employer-sponsored plans or Medicaid, which PDP Sponsors must coordinate with to avoid duplication and ensure proper benefit integration."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d33402aba37c5664514afa00a872b8ae</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CMS'S INSTRUCTIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"DOCUMENT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"CMS provides specific instructions for notice dissemination."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a8d49cc5f599bfb3f6f139071bb0cfac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BENEFITS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PROGRAM FEATURE"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The range of prescription drugs and services covered under a Part D plan."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-647561dd6831e3ae72c2d43faf5b0b9f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SUBPART J OF 42 CFR PART 423&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"REGULATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"This regulatory subpart outlines the coordination requirements between PDP Sponsors and other prescription drug coverage programs, including SPAPs, to ensure seamless benefit delivery."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d33402aba37c5664514afa00a872b8ae</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;42 CFR § 423.508&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"REGULATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A federal regulation that outlines the consequences of terminating PBP offerings."&lt;SEP&gt;"A federal regulation that outlines the process for notifying enrollees of contract modifications."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a8d49cc5f599bfb3f6f139071bb0cfac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COST-SHARING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"FINANCIAL TERM"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The portion of drug costs that beneficiaries are responsible for, such as copayments and deductibles."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-647561dd6831e3ae72c2d43faf5b0b9f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MEDICARE SECONDARY PAYER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Medicare Secondary Payer (MSP) procedures govern situations where another payer (e.g., employer or liability insurer) is responsible for payment before Medicare. PDP Sponsors must follow these procedures to avoid improper payments."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d33402aba37c5664514afa00a872b8ae</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CONTRACT MODIFICATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ACTION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A change to the contract made by mutual consent."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a8d49cc5f599bfb3f6f139071bb0cfac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NEGOTIATIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PROCESS"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A formal discussion between CMS and PDP Sponsor to finalize bid terms and plan renewal."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-647561dd6831e3ae72c2d43faf5b0b9f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;42 CFR § 423.462&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"REGULATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"This regulation details the Medicare Secondary Payer procedures that PDP Sponsors must follow, including identifying and reporting primary payer responsibilities."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d33402aba37c5664514afa00a872b8ae</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NOTIFICATION PROCESS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PROCEDURE"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The process for notifying Medicare enrollees of changes, as specified by CMS."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a8d49cc5f599bfb3f6f139071bb0cfac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BENEFIT PLAN RENEWAL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PROCESS"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The process of extending a Part D plan for the next program year."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-647561dd6831e3ae72c2d43faf5b0b9f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PART D BENEFITS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"SERVICE"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Part D benefits are prescription drug coverage provided under Medicare Part D, which PDP Sponsors are required to deliver in their approved service areas."&lt;SEP&gt;"The prescription drug benefits provided under Medicare Part D."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-98acde792b4efcfd60a0e94224e24870&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d33402aba37c5664514afa00a872b8ae</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TIMEFRAMES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"TIME PERIOD"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The timeframes for notification are specified by CMS."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a8d49cc5f599bfb3f6f139071bb0cfac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STATE LAW&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"REGULATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Laws enacted by individual U.S. states that apply to PDP Sponsors, unless overridden by federal law."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-647561dd6831e3ae72c2d43faf5b0b9f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SERVICE AREA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"GEOGRAPHIC AREA"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A service area is a defined geographic region approved by CMS for a PDP Sponsor to offer Part D benefits. The sponsor must operate within this area."&lt;SEP&gt;"The regions where a PDP Sponsor provides Part D benefits."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d33402aba37c5664514afa00a872b8ae&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-647561dd6831e3ae72c2d43faf5b0b9f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TIMELY TRANSFER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ACTION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The act of transferring data and files without delay."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a8d49cc5f599bfb3f6f139071bb0cfac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEDERAL LAW&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"REGULATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"National laws that take precedence over state laws in Medicare Part D."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-647561dd6831e3ae72c2d43faf5b0b9f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;45 CFR PART 80&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"REGULATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Regulations implementing Title VI of the Civil Rights Act of 1964."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bb09bdd246d7da48cb03f821334b1a33</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PHARMACY NETWORK&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A network of pharmacies contracted by the PDP Sponsor to dispense prescription drugs, which must be approved by CMS."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d33402aba37c5664514afa00a872b8ae</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NEW CONTRACT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"DOCUMENT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A new contract that CMS cannot enter into with the PDP Sponsor or related organizations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a8d49cc5f599bfb3f6f139071bb0cfac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SUBPART I OF 42 CFR PART 423&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"REGULATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Federal regulation outlining the preemption of state law by federal law in Medicare Part D."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-647561dd6831e3ae72c2d43faf5b0b9f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FORMULARY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"DOCUMENT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A formulary is a list of covered prescription drugs approved by the PDP Sponsor and CMS, which determines which medications are available under the plan."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d33402aba37c5664514afa00a872b8ae</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SERVICE AREA EXPANSION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ACTION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"An expansion of service areas by CMS is restricted for 2 years."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a8d49cc5f599bfb3f6f139071bb0cfac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;42 CFR § 423.410&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"REGULATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Federal regulation allowing waivers for state licensure requirements in Medicare Part D."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-647561dd6831e3ae72c2d43faf5b0b9f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;42 CFR § 423.120&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"REGULATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"This regulation specifies the requirements for pharmacy networks and formularies used by PDP Sponsors, including CMS approval and compliance with coverage standards."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d33402aba37c5664514afa00a872b8ae</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;42 CFR § 423.508(F)&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"REGULATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A federal regulation that defines covered persons in the context of contract termination."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a8d49cc5f599bfb3f6f139071bb0cfac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;THREE CONSECUTIVE PROGRAM YEARS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"TIME PERIOD"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The duration for which a waiver remains valid."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-647561dd6831e3ae72c2d43faf5b0b9f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TITLE VI OF THE CIVIL RIGHTS ACT OF 1964&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"LAW"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A federal law prohibiting discrimination on the basis of race, color, or national origin."&lt;SEP&gt;"A federal law that prohibits discrimination on the basis of race, color, or national origin in programs receiving federal financial assistance, applicable to PDP Sponsors."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1ba6b4dc9d71dff813e0972c4e6c371&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb09bdd246d7da48cb03f821334b1a33</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OUT-OF-NETWORK PHARMACIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Pharmacies not part of the PDP Sponsor’s contracted network, which the sponsor must still cover under certain conditions as required by 42 CFR § 423.124."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d33402aba37c5664514afa00a872b8ae</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;UP TO 2 YEARS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"TIME PERIOD"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A restriction period of up to 2 years applies to new contracts or expansions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a8d49cc5f599bfb3f6f139071bb0cfac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LICENSURE WAIVER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"LEGAL DOCUMENT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A waiver allowing a PDP Sponsor to operate without a state license."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-647561dd6831e3ae72c2d43faf5b0b9f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;42 CFR § 423.124&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"REGULATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"This regulation governs how PDP Sponsors must provide benefits through out-of-network pharmacies, ensuring access to prescription drugs even when pharmacies are not in the approved network."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d33402aba37c5664514afa00a872b8ae</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OFFERING OF PBPS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ACTION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The act of providing plan benefit packages in a region."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a8d49cc5f599bfb3f6f139071bb0cfac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PDP REGIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"GEOGRAPHIC AREA"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Specific areas within a service area where Part D plans are offered."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-647561dd6831e3ae72c2d43faf5b0b9f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;POINT OF SERVICE SYSTEMS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"SYSTEM"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Point of service systems are mechanisms used by PDP Sponsors to process and adjudicate prescription drug claims at the time of dispensing, ensuring timely and efficient payment."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d33402aba37c5664514afa00a872b8ae</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RESUME OFFERING PLANS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ACTION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The act of reapplying to offer plans in a region."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a8d49cc5f599bfb3f6f139071bb0cfac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CONTRACT TERMINATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PROCESS"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The cancellation of a PDP Sponsor’s contract with CMS."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-647561dd6831e3ae72c2d43faf5b0b9f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ADJUDICATE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ACTION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The process of evaluating and approving or denying a prescription drug claim based on plan coverage rules."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d33402aba37c5664514afa00a872b8ae</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SOCIAL SECURITY ACT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"LAW"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The Act includes sections 1860D-1 through 1860D-43, which are central to the operation of the Medicare Prescription Drug Plan."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Social Security Act includes sections 1860D-1 through 1860D-43, which govern the operation of a Voluntary Medicare Prescription Drug Plan."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-acb96757aadb929819265d4fddd43c2d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NON-RENEWAL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PROCESS"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The decision not to extend a PDP Sponsor’s contract upon expiration."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-647561dd6831e3ae72c2d43faf5b0b9f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;UNDERSERVED AREAS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"GEOGRAPHIC AREA"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Geographic regions with limited access to pharmacy services, where special provisions allow for alternative claim adjudication methods."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d33402aba37c5664514afa00a872b8ae</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOLUNTARY MEDICARE PRESCRIPTION DRUG PLAN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PROGRAM"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A program authorized under the Social Security Act for the provision of prescription drug benefits to Medicare beneficiaries."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-acb96757aadb929819265d4fddd43c2d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;QUALIFIED TO OFFER A PDP PLAN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"STATUS"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The legal and operational standing required for a PDP Sponsor to provide Part D benefits."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-647561dd6831e3ae72c2d43faf5b0b9f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;I/T/U PHARMACIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Independent, Temporary, or Urgent pharmacies, as defined in 42 CFR § 423.100, which serve patients in emergency or transitional situations and may require special handling of claims."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d33402aba37c5664514afa00a872b8ae</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;42 CFR § 423.503&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"REGULATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"This regulation determines the eligibility of an entity to operate a Voluntary Medicare Prescription Drug Plan under CMS administration."&lt;SEP&gt;"This regulation governs the eligibility criteria for entities seeking to operate a Medicare Prescription Drug Plan."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-acb96757aadb929819265d4fddd43c2d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OPERATING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ACTION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The act of providing Part D benefits in a specific geographic area."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-647561dd6831e3ae72c2d43faf5b0b9f</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;42 CFR § 423.505(P)&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"REGULATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A federal regulation requiring the maintenance and implementation of a business continuity plan."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bb09bdd246d7da48cb03f821334b1a33</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LONG-TERM CARE PHARMACIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Pharmacies that serve residents of long-term care facilities, such as nursing homes, and are defined in 42 CFR § 423.100."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d33402aba37c5664514afa00a872b8ae</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SECTIONS 1860D-1 THROUGH 1860D-43&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"LAW"</data>
  <data key="d4">"These sections of the Social Security Act establish the legal framework for the Medicare Prescription Drug Benefit."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-acb96757aadb929819265d4fddd43c2d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;KEY MANAGEMENT OR EXECUTIVE STAFF&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Key management or executive staff are individuals within the PDP Sponsor or its subcontractors who may be involved in investigations or legal actions related to government payments."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-089a3e7f57f00ea7d36a53726e96e60c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;42 CFR § 423.505(B)(17)&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"REGULATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"This regulation specifies exceptions to the point of service system requirement, allowing alternative claim processing in underserved areas, I/T/U pharmacies, and long-term care pharmacies."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d33402aba37c5664514afa00a872b8ae</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CONTRACT ID&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"IDENTIFIER"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A unique identifier assigned to the contract between CMS and the PDP Sponsor."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-acb96757aadb929819265d4fddd43c2d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MAJOR SHAREHOLDERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Major shareholders are individuals or entities owning 5% or more of the PDP Sponsor or its firm, and are subject to investigations or legal actions by government agencies."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-089a3e7f57f00ea7d36a53726e96e60c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;REASONABLE AND RELEVANT STANDARD TERMS AND CONDITIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"These are the criteria used by a PDP Sponsor to evaluate and contract with pharmacies, ensuring fairness, consistency, and compliance with federal standards."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d33402aba37c5664514afa00a872b8ae</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;2025 SOLICITATION FOR APPLICATIONS FOR MEDICARE PRESCRIPTION DRUG PLAN CONTRACTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"DOCUMENT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A document released on January 9, 2024, that outlines the application process and requirements for operating a Medicare Prescription Drug Plan."&lt;SEP&gt;"A document released on January 9, 2024, that outlines the requirements for applying to operate a Medicare Prescription Drug Plan."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-acb96757aadb929819265d4fddd43c2d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GOVERNMENT AGENCY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Government agencies, including State and Federal entities, are responsible for initiating investigations, legal actions, or arbitration against the PDP Sponsor or its subcontractors."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-089a3e7f57f00ea7d36a53726e96e60c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BUSINESS CONTINUITY PLAN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A plan developed, maintained, and implemented by a PDP Sponsor to ensure continued operations during disruptions, as required by 42 CFR § 423.505(p)."&lt;SEP&gt;"A plan that must be maintained and implemented as required by 42 CFR § 423.505(p)."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1ba6b4dc9d71dff813e0972c4e6c371&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb09bdd246d7da48cb03f821334b1a33</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STANDARD CONTRACTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"DOCUMENT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Standardized contract templates provided by the PDP Sponsor to pharmacies, which must be made available upon request and in accordance with specified timelines."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d33402aba37c5664514afa00a872b8ae</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;§§ 1860D-22(A) AND 1860D-31&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"LAW"</data>
  <data key="d4">"These sections of the Social Security Act are excluded from the scope of the contract."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-acb96757aadb929819265d4fddd43c2d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HEALTHCARE SERVICES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"SERVICE"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Healthcare services are a category of services for which payments from governmental entities are subject to investigation and scrutiny."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-089a3e7f57f00ea7d36a53726e96e60c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SECTION 504 OF THE REHABILITATION ACT OF 1973&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"LAW"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A federal law prohibiting discrimination on the basis of disability."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-bb09bdd246d7da48cb03f821334b1a33</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;42 CFR § 423.505(B)(18)&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"REGULATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"This regulation mandates that PDP Sponsors must contract with any pharmacy meeting their reasonable and relevant standards and make standard contracts available on request within specified timeframes."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d33402aba37c5664514afa00a872b8ae</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MEDICARE VOLUNTARY PRESCRIPTION DRUG PLAN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PROGRAM"</data>
