</node>
<node id="&quot;CMS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"CMS (Centers for Medicare &amp; Medicaid Services) is a federal agency responsible for overseeing Medicare programs and receiving notifications from the PDP Sponsor."&lt;SEP&gt;"CMS (Centers for Medicare &amp; Medicaid Services) is a federal agency responsible for overseeing Medicare programs, including the Part D Prescription Drug Plan (PDP). It has the authority to terminate or non-renew a PDP Sponsor's contract if the waiver expiration leads to ineligibility to offer a PDP plan in any region."&lt;SEP&gt;"CMS (Centers for Medicare &amp; Medicaid Services) is the federal agency responsible for administering Medicare, including the authority to terminate contracts with PDP Sponsors under specific regulations."&lt;SEP&gt;"CMS (Centers for Medicare &amp; Medicaid Services) is the federal agency responsible for approving notices and scripts."&lt;SEP&gt;"CMS (Centers for Medicare &amp; Medicaid Services) is the federal agency that contracts with an entity to track Medicare beneficiaries' true out-of-pocket costs and oversees the PDP Sponsor's compliance."&lt;SEP&gt;"CMS (Centers for Medicare &amp; Medicaid Services) is the federal agency that establishes fees and regulations for cost sharing in the Medicare Part D program."&lt;SEP&gt;"CMS agrees to perform its obligations to the PDP Sponsor in accordance with the Act and related regulations."&lt;SEP&gt;"CMS has the authority to assess compliance and initiate enforcement actions against PDP Sponsors."&lt;SEP&gt;"CMS is a federal agency that administers Medicare and enters into contracts with PDP Sponsors."&lt;SEP&gt;"CMS is the federal agency responsible for releasing public data on Part D programs, in compliance with Subpart K of 42 CFR Part 423."&lt;SEP&gt;"CMS refers to the Centers for Medicare &amp; Medicaid Services, a U.S. federal agency responsible for administering Medicare programs, including the Medicare Advantage Attestation of Benefit Plan. It is referenced in contracting materials and is updated annually to reflect PDP Sponsor's approved bids for the next contract year."&lt;SEP&gt;"Centers for Medicare &amp; Medicaid Services, the federal agency overseeing Medicare programs."&lt;SEP&gt;"Centers for Medicare &amp; Medicaid Services, which has authority to remove regions from a sponsor’s service area."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Centers for Medicare &amp; Medicaid Services, the federal agency responsible for administering Medicare programs."&lt;SEP&gt;"The federal agency that contracts with an entity to track out-of-pocket costs for Medicare beneficiaries."&lt;SEP&gt;"The federal agency that receives and monitors complaints against PDP Sponsors."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1ba6b4dc9d71dff813e0972c4e6c371&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-acb96757aadb929819265d4fddd43c2d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89bdab9933b704535281ee7396b3c0c8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a8d49cc5f599bfb3f6f139071bb0cfac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-647561dd6831e3ae72c2d43faf5b0b9f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a77fb65c6800edbf628ea7f71f893ea5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-089a3e7f57f00ea7d36a53726e96e60c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-98acde792b4efcfd60a0e94224e24870&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d33402aba37c5664514afa00a872b8ae&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b14ea02aabc3c1d74ff07de937978aa9</data>
</node>
