</node>
<node id="&quot;PDP SPONSOR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">The PDP Sponsor is a private entity approved by the Centers for Medicare &amp; Medicaid Services (CMS) to operate a Voluntary Medicare Prescription Drug Plan (PDP) under Medicare Part D. As a federally regulated organization, the PDP Sponsor must meet stringent federal and state requirements to maintain eligibility, including obtaining and maintaining valid waivers and adhering to all CMS regulations. The PDP Sponsor is responsible for administering the Medicare Part D Prescription Drug Plan, which includes calculating and collecting premiums from beneficiaries in accordance with 42 CFR §§ 423.286 and 423.293, submitting approved bids annually, and updating drug reimbursement standards at least every seven days starting January 1 to reflect current market prices.

The PDP Sponsor agrees to enter into a business associate agreement with any entity contracted by CMS to track Medicare beneficiaries’ true out-of-pocket costs and is required to comply with payment obligations established by CMS for cost-sharing related to enrollment, as mandated by 42 CFR § 423.6. The entity must also comply with all applicable federal laws and regulations, including those related to fraud, waste, and abuse, such as the False Claims Act and anti-kickback provisions, and must adhere to anti-discrimination laws and regulations.

The PDP Sponsor is bound by contractual obligations, including a two-year restriction on reapplying to offer plans in a region after terminating its contract with CMS, as outlined in 42 CFR § 423.510. While the PDP Sponsor has the right to choose not to renew its contract for any reason, provided proper notice is given, it may only terminate its contract under the specific conditions defined by CMS. Additionally, the PDP Sponsor must attest to not altering the original contract terms presented by CMS and agrees that any modifications made by the Sponsor are not binding.

The PDP Sponsor is responsible for addressing and resolving complaints received by CMS and is subject to enforcement actions if found out of compliance with Part D requirements. The entity operates within the healthcare and prescription drug services sector and may be subject to investigations, legal actions, or arbitration by government agencies related to payments from federal and state entities. Overall, the PDP Sponsor is an organization determined eligible by CMS to sponsor and administer Medicare Part D Prescription Drug Plans, operating under strict regulatory oversight and contractual commitments.</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a1ba6b4dc9d71dff813e0972c4e6c371&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-acb96757aadb929819265d4fddd43c2d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89bdab9933b704535281ee7396b3c0c8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a8d49cc5f599bfb3f6f139071bb0cfac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-647561dd6831e3ae72c2d43faf5b0b9f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb09bdd246d7da48cb03f821334b1a33&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a77fb65c6800edbf628ea7f71f893ea5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-089a3e7f57f00ea7d36a53726e96e60c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-98acde792b4efcfd60a0e94224e24870&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d33402aba37c5664514afa00a872b8ae&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b14ea02aabc3c1d74ff07de937978aa9</data>
